 The First Lady, Mrs. Aisha Buhari, arrived the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja at 4.30am via a British Airways flight on Sunday two months after she left the country for the United Kingdom. According to a terse statement from Suleiman Haruna, her Director of Information released on Sunday morning, on her arrival, Mrs. Buhari told reporters that she was happy to be home after a well-deserved rest. She also confirmed that she was fully rejuvenated to continue the work of improving the health and well-being of women, children and other vulnerable Nigerians. The statement said used the opportunity to thank her husband, family and well-wishers for their support and encouragement. On hand to receive her were wives of present and former and governors and many associates. The president’s wife had announced her planned return to the country at about 8.56pm on Saturday while leaving London. Making the announcement on her Twitter handle, @AishaMBuhari, the first lady said Mrs. Modupe Oguntade, the wife of Nigeria’s High Commissioner to the United Kingdom, Retired Justice George Oguntade, was seeing her off. “Wife of the Nigerian Ambassador to the United Kingdom, Mrs Modupe Oguntade seeing me off. Thank you so much madam,” she tweeted. On Saturday night, online news portal, TheCable reported that Aisha left Nigeria in August for Saudi Arabia for the lesser hajj and from Saudi Arabia headed for the United Kingdom. According to the online medium, Aisha was in the United Kingdom for medical treatment. Her stay in the UK for over two months had generated a range of controversies at home.